This is because `malloc()` instantiates memory, but does not initialise it.
If you&#39;re not immediately working with the memory, it may be prudent to call `memset(buffer, 0, MAX_SIZE * sizeof(key_value));` just after `malloc()`, to zero-out all allocated memory locations.

